{"id": 6, "ts": 1778865357.7729416, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 1, "agent": "agent_1", "message": "From the information I have, the candidates show the following key attributes:\n- **Candidate A**: Strong at anticipating dangerous situations, seeing complex connections, excellent spatial vision, and very good leadership. Weaknesses are being unorganized and not taking criticism well. I have no data on reliability or crew\u2011cooperation.\n- **Candidate B**: Keeps calm in a crisis, is described as 100\u202f% reliable, good at assessing weather, and has excellent computer skills. Reported downsides are a tendency to be grumpy and uncooperative. I lack any explicit information on teamwork or crew\u2011cooperation strengths.\n- **Candidate C**: Makes correct decisions quickly, handles stress well, and creates a positive atmosphere with the crew. However, he has difficulty communicating ideas, is regarded as egocentric, and is not very willing to pursue further education.\n- **Candidate D**: Responds adequately to unexpected events, concentrates very well, solves problems extremely well, and takes responsibility seriously. Weak points are being regarded as arrogant and having relatively weak leadership skills. I have no explicit note on calmness under pressure or crew\u2011cooperation.\nGiven the long\u2011distance pilot role\u2019s emphasis on reliability, calmness under pressure, sound decision\u2011making, and crew cooperation, Candidate\u202fB appears strongest on reliability and calmness, but I need to confirm his teamwork abilities. I also would like to know whether Candidate\u202fD remains calm under pressure, as that could offset some of his leadership concerns.\n**Questions for the other agents:**\n1. Do you have any information on Candidate\u202fB\u2019s strengths regarding teamwork or crew cooperation?\n2. Do you have any information on Candidate\u202fD\u2019s calmness or composure under pressure?\nBased on the current picture, I am leaning